{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-9222].
  {panel}

We have a bunch of old epics that are showing up in plan mode. If the jira ticket that represents the epic is closed, it shouldn't be available in plan mode automatically. I should not have to manually mark them done.

+Example use cases:+

- using a filter to filter not only by issue count, but also "More than 3 Critical issues", or "More than 2 issues of type X" - then apply color highlighting accordingly;
- applying constraints to limit Issues assigned to one user.

At the moment it is not possible to show only certain subtasks of a story in plan mode. Quick filters like

{noformat}
type = "SubTaskType"
{noformat}

show no stories. In combination with GHS-9178 we would be able to get an easy overview of the required effort for certain aspects (e.g. subtask types) of a story.

h3. Manual testing
* Round of testing to ensure that changes to permissions are okay;
* Sprints on multiple boards;
* Reports - sprint picking, sprint data, past sprints, sprints which had issues removed before they were started;
* JQL searching of sprints, JQL functions for sprints

h3. Automated testing
* Ensuring that automated tests are working;
* Ensure that tests cover the correct things.

The {{ChartBoardAction.doSetCurveColor}} method is vulnerable to persistent XSS when saving an unsanitized {{color}} parameter in user preferences. The set method isn’t protected from XSRF, allowing exploitation from remote attackers.

File: greenhopper\src\main\java\com\pyxis\greenhopper\jira\Actions\ChartBoardAction.java

{code:title=ChartBoardAction.java|borderStyle=solid}
